At the start of the World Championships in Athletics, new details about the doping scandal in Russia are being revealed - and they destroy the little of credibility that Russian sports had recovered, even to some extent, at the beginning of the year. In January 2019, the Moscow doping laboratory finally delivered the required samples from 2012 to 2015 to the World Anti Doping Agency (Wada) .Now it turned out that they were falsified.
In December 2014, systematic fraud in the Russian sport was revealed. Consequently, Wada had subsequently banned the Russian Anti-Doping Agency (Rusada) for three years. During this time Russian athletes were not completely banished from the world stage. After an individual examination, the International Olympic Committee had around 270 athletes of the country compete under neutral flag at the 2016 Summer Games in Rio Rio, at the Winter Games in February 2018, 168 Russian athletes were part the the start. They were allowed to take participate in the World Cups in the various sports and in the summer even the sothe er World Cup took place in Russia with the host as participant.
Positive Findings Missing
The following September, Wada ada lifted Rusada ban ban, but demanded access to the laboratory and the samples in question. The data were intended to provide information on the possible extent of cover-up of doping cases in state doping ing. They were intended to help to subsequently punish athletes, and were finally delivered three months later.
However, the chairman of the Independent Integrity Commission (AIU) of the World Athletics Federation (IAAF) has now confirmed that the doping data from the Moscow analytical laboratory have been manipulated. " Yes. We received the data nine months ago. We should check whether the task force has received the correct data, " said David HHowman in an interview Friday with " Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung. " " We have noted a number of discrepancy between data from the Wada from a whistleblower whistleblower and those it received from the Russians in January. " Many positive findings were missing that were mentioned in the McLaren report.
The World Cup not affected
This is the confirmation of the IAAF's stance: The Athletics Federation is the only organisation that is heres to the spell of Russia. At the World Cup in Doha, 30 Russian athletes will compete under a neutral flag. They had to prove that they are training outside the Russian system and undergo tests.
